<sect1 id="arch_page_front_1arch_overview">
<title>Overview</title>
<para>The ARCH library is a repository for all architecture-dependent code. It isolates all platform dependencies (and confusing #ifdefs) into one small library and also serves as a common area for documentation of these multi-platform issues.</para>
<para>The high-level grouping of the classes/functions is: <itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___bits" kindref="compound">Bits </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___multithreading" kindref="compound">Multithreading </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___math" kindref="compound">Math </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___strings" kindref="compound">Strings </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___system_functions" kindref="compound">System Functions </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___memory" kindref="compound">Memory Management </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___diagnostics" kindref="compound">Diagnostics </ref> </para>
</listitem>
<listitem><para><ref refid="group__group__arch___symbol_visibility" kindref="compound">Symbol Visibility </ref></para>
</listitem>
</itemizedlist>
